<subSubSection id="6AE1642E194165840675D554B6F3A484" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="comments">
<paragraph id="4C6BE6891D68B5F0D9FA75C01576D548" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="41C7A6435A5D87AB06688F4BAB2AFA77" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
When 
<bibRefCitation id="42F3D8684B480011677F34A78CAB715E" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Sydow and Sydow (1915)</bibRefCitation>
published the name 
<taxonomicName id="82D212B8056C33D5CD8FA592C1DA853A" class="Pucciniomycetes" genus="Hemileia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hemileia scheffleri" order="Pucciniales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="scheffleri">Hemileia scheffleri</taxonomicName>
, they attributed it only to Syd., however, the name is clearly based on 
<taxonomicName id="8EA19E3E1B597764FBC58CDCDB82B7A4" class="Pucciniomycetes" genus="Uredo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Uredo scheffleri" order="Pucciniales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="scheffleri">Uredo scheffleri</taxonomicName>
i.e. both names are based on the same type specimen. With the new ICN, this name in 
<taxonomicName id="6C59E400FA5DD6A30FE706FE95C246DB" class="Pucciniomycetes" genus="Hemileia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hemileia" order="Pucciniales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">Hemileia</taxonomicName>
is the correct name for this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
